Privacy Policy
Plato Fetcher (“the App”) is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how your information is handled when you use the App with Dropbox.
1. Information Collection and Storage
	•	The App does not collect, store, or use any personal information from users.
	•	No user data is transmitted to or stored on any external servers.
2. Dropbox Access and Data Usage
	•	The App only requests permission to access the `/Apps/Plato Fetcher` folder in your Dropbox account.
	•	The App only reads data within this specific folder to perform its core functionality.
	•	The App does not access, modify, or read any other files or folders in your Dropbox account.
3. Data Security
	•	Since the App does not collect or store any user data, there is no risk of data leakage or unauthorized sharing.
4. Third-Party Sharing
	•	The App does not share any data with third parties.
5. Changes to This Policy
	•	This Privacy Policy may be updated in the future. Any changes will be posted within the App or on the official website.
6. Contact
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact: your email/contact information.
Summary:
Plato Fetcher does not collect, store, or share any user data. The App only reads data from the `/Apps/Plato Fetcher` folder in your Dropbox account and does not access any other information.
Feel free to edit the contact information or add any specific details related to your app or company. This policy is compliant with Dropbox’s app submission requirements for privacy.
